This paper discusses a new hardware-assisted method to resist code reuse attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of physical unclonable functions (PUFs) and encryption/decryption operations, which are commonly used in the areas of computer architecture (cs.AR), software engineering (cs.SE), and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper proposes a new method for control flow checking, which may be relevant to programming languages (cs.PL).
